// After creating this, in VS Code click the environment name in the bottom-right status bar 
// (or Ctrl+Shift+P → "Rest Client: Switch Environment") and pick dev — that's what makes {{baseUrl}} etc. resolve.
// baseurl or usertoken , admin token , categoryid , productid , ticketid , addressid in .vscode/settings.json

### Create Product (admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "description": "Ergonomic wireless mouse",
  "price": 799,
  "stock": 50,
  "category": "{{categoryId}}"
}

### Get All Products (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products

### Get Single Product (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}

### Update Product (admin only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "price": 899,
  "stock": 45
}

### Delete Product (admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Create Product with Image Upload (admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Wireless Keyboard
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="price"

1299
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="stock"

30
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

{{categoryId}}
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="images"; filename="keyboard.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-image.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary--